[Scientists are still working on human immunity against WNV. Currently,
there is no WNV vaccine available for humans. The WNV vaccine for horses
has been licensed. The effectiveness of this vaccine in preventing West
Nile virus infections in horses has yet to be fully evaluated. There is
hope that a vaccine will become available in the next few years. - Mod.RY]
